## 1. Purpose

This implementation guide explains how to apply the OPRMT™ Framework in practical prompt engineering, documentation, workflow design, prompt libraries, AI-assisted business systems, and repository-governed prompt assets.

This guide is not the official framework standard. It is an operational guide for applying the framework consistently.

---

## 2. Implementation Principle

OPRMT™ should be implemented as a structured instruction system, not as casual prompt wording.

Every implementation should define:

```text
O — Objective
P — Parameters
R — Results
M — Method
T — Tools
```

The structure exists to improve clarity, repeatability, auditability, and review quality.

---

## 3. When to Use OPRMT™

Use OPRMT™ when the task requires:

- Repeatable prompt construction
- Professional AI workflow design
- Clear output requirements
- Auditable prompt structure
- Prompt library development
- Prompt cluster packaging
- AI assistant instructions
- Business process automation
- Documentation generation
- Curriculum or assessment design
- Compliance-oriented output review
- Prompt quality scoring

Avoid using full OPRMT™ structure for trivial one-line tasks unless consistency or auditability is required.

---

## 4. Implementation Levels

| Level | Use Case | Required Structure |
|---|---|---|
| Level 1 — Basic | Simple personal or internal prompt | Objective + Results |
| Level 2 — Structured | Reusable work prompt | Objective + Parameters + Results |
| Level 3 — Operational | Business workflow or documentation task | Objective + Parameters + Results + Method |
| Level 4 — Governed | Repository, product, course, or prompt library asset | Full OPRMT™ structure |
| Level 5 — Compliance Reviewed | PCE or DOAS™ scored prompt/output | Full OPRMT™ + validation criteria |

